---
import Base from '../layouts/Base.astro';
import { getAllProblems } from '../lib/problems.js';

const problems = getAllProblems();
const solved = problems.filter(p => p.status === 'solved').length;
---
<Base>
  <div class="home-landing">
    <blockquote class="chandrasekhar-quote">
      <p>
        &ldquo;In my entire scientific life, extending over forty-five years, the most
        shattering experience has been the realization that an exact solution of
        Einstein&apos;s equations of general relativity, discovered by the New Zealand
        mathematician, Roy Kerr, provides the absolutely exact representation of
        untold numbers of massive black holes that populate the universe.&rdquo;
      </p>
      <footer>
        &mdash; S. Chandrasekhar, <em>Shakespeare, Newton, and Beethoven</em>, 1975
      </footer>
    </blockquote>

    <div class="home-intro-below-quote">
      <p>
        Most black holes in the observable universe are rotating. The Kerr spacetime &mdash; Roy Kerr&apos;s 1963 exact solution to Einstein&apos;s vacuum equations &mdash; is the geometry that describes them all. It is one of the most important objects in mathematical physics: simple enough to write in a single formula, rich enough to have resisted complete mathematical understanding for over sixty years.
      </p>
      <p>
        This site exists to track that resistance. It is a living database of open problems in the rigorous mathematical study of Kerr black holes &mdash; problems in stability, singularities, scattering, uniqueness, and spectral theory. Every problem is stated precisely, traced to a primary source, and updated as the field moves. The goal is to make the frontier visible: to show what is known, what is partial, and what remains genuinely open.
      </p>
      <p>
        We are at an unusual moment. Formal proof assistants like Lean are making it possible to verify arguments at a scale and speed previously unimaginable, and AI systems are beginning to contribute meaningfully to research-level mathematics &mdash; finding references, closing partial arguments, and in some cases generating genuine new proofs. The Kerr problem landscape is exactly the kind of structured, precisely-stated territory where these tools can have real impact. This database is designed with that future in mind: a shared map of the open problems, so that human mathematicians, formal verification projects, and AI systems can orient themselves and push the frontier forward together.
      </p>
    </div>

    <p class="home-count-line">
      There are {problems.length} problems in this database, of which {solved} have been fully solved.
    </p>

    <p class="home-prose">
      The Kerr spacetime &mdash; the exact solution to Einstein&apos;s vacuum equations describing a rotating black hole &mdash; lies at the centre of modern mathematical general relativity. Discovered by Roy Kerr in 1963, it remains the subject of deep open problems spanning stability, singularities, scattering, and uniqueness. This database tracks those problems, their current status, and the partial results that surround them.
    </p>

    <div class="home-columns">
      <section class="home-col">
        <h2 class="home-pill">Recent progress</h2>
        <div class="home-col-stack">
          <div class="home-progress-item">
            <a href="/problems/K-001">K-001 &nbsp; Full nonlinear stability of subextremal Kerr</a>
            <div class="home-progress-date">(April 2026)</div>
          </div>
          <div class="home-progress-item">
            <a href="/problems/K-101">K-101 &nbsp; Strong Cosmic Censorship threshold for Kerr interiors</a>
            <div class="home-progress-date">(April 2026)</div>
          </div>
          <div class="home-progress-item">
            <a href="/problems/K-201">K-201 &nbsp; Nonlinear codimension-1 stability of extremal Kerr</a>
            <div class="home-progress-date">(April 2026)</div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </section>

      <section class="home-col">
        <h2 class="home-pill">Key references</h2>
        <div class="home-col-stack">
          <div class="home-ref-item">
            Giorgi, Klainerman, Szeftel &mdash; Full stability of Schwarzschild{' '}
            <a href="https://arxiv.org/abs/2205.14808">arXiv:2205.14808</a>
          </div>
          <div class="home-ref-item">
            Dafermos, Luk &mdash; Interior of dynamical vacuum black holes{' '}
            <a href="https://arxiv.org/abs/1710.01722">arXiv:1710.01722</a>
          </div>
          <div class="home-ref-item">
            Teukolsky &mdash; The Kerr metric (review){' '}
            <a href="https://arxiv.org/abs/1410.2130">arXiv:1410.2130</a>
          </div>
        </div>
      </section>

      <section class="home-col">
        <h2 class="home-pill">Open &rarr; solved</h2>
        <p class="home-solved-placeholder">
          Problems whose status changes to solved will be listed here with the date this site was updated.
        </p>
      </section>
    </div>
  </div>
</Base>

<style>
  .chandrasekhar-quote {
    background: #f0f4f0;
    border: 1px solid #ccc;
    border-radius: 8px;
    padding: 1.5rem 2rem;
    max-width: 780px;
    margin: 0 auto 2rem;
  }
  .chandrasekhar-quote p {
    margin: 0;
  }
  .chandrasekhar-quote footer {
    text-align: right;
    font-size: 0.85rem;
    color: #555;
    font-style: italic;
    margin-top: 1rem;
  }

  .home-intro-below-quote {
    max-width: 62ch;
    margin: 0 0 1.5rem;
  }
  .home-intro-below-quote p {
    margin: 0 0 1rem;
  }
  .home-intro-below-quote p:last-child {
    margin-bottom: 0;
  }

  .home-count-line {
    margin: 0 0 1rem;
  }

  .home-prose {
    margin: 0;
    max-width: 62ch;
  }

  .home-pill {
    display: inline-block;
    border: 1px solid #999;
    border-radius: 999px;
    padding: 0.3em 1.1em;
    font-family: "Courier New", Courier, monospace;
    font-size: 0.78rem;
    letter-spacing: 0.06em;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    background: transparent;
    color: #333;
    font-weight: 400;
    margin: 0 0 0.75rem;
  }

  .home-columns {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: 1fr 1fr 1fr;
    gap: 2rem;
    margin-top: 2.5rem;
    align-items: start;
  }

  .home-col-stack {
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    gap: 0.8rem;
  }

  .home-progress-item a {
    color: var(--link, #0066cc);
    text-decoration: none;
  }
  .home-progress-item a:hover {
    text-decoration: underline;
  }

  .home-progress-date {
    font-size: 0.8rem;
    color: #777;
    margin-top: 0.15rem;
  }

  .home-ref-item {
    font-size: inherit;
  }
  .home-ref-item a {
    color: var(--link, #0066cc);
    text-decoration: none;
  }
  .home-ref-item a:hover {
    text-decoration: underline;
  }

  .home-solved-placeholder {
    margin: 0;
    font-style: italic;
    color: #777;
  }

  @media (max-width: 600px) {
    .home-columns {
      grid-template-columns: 1fr;
    }
  }
</style>
